  "policy": {
    "phases": {
      "hot": {
        "min_age": "0d",
        "actions": {
          "rollover": { "max_primary_shard_size": "50GB", "max_age": "1d" },
          "set_priority": { "priority": 100 }
        }
      },
      "warm": {
        "min_age": "7d",
        "actions": {
          "shrink": { "number_of_shards": 1 },
          "forcemerge": { "max_num_segments": 1 },
          "set_priority": { "priority": 50 }
        }
      },
      "cold": {
        "min_age": "30d",
        "actions": {
          "searchable_snapshot": { "snapshot_repository": "s3-repo" },
          "set_priority": { "priority": 0 }
        }
      },
      "delete": {
        "min_age": "90d",
        "actions": { "delete": {} }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

This is the single most important cost control mechanism — it ensures only ~7 days of data (~2.3TB assuming even distribution) sits on expensive hot storage.

